        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-27T00:16:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In fetch, cli.GetConfig returns an error if the config doesn\u0027t exist. I changed it to ignore config.ErrNoConfig.",
      "parentUuid": "6cbdb078_ce08f3e5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 7,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 7,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "9b42c4d0d9ad2659dbfca0257bd7c12babc80d74",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0ae7a0c2_c05a200b",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 18,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-25T01:21:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "0) Isn\u0027t it better to only consider configs which are intended (ie at the same revision) as consistent?\n\nie, suppose I modified a VMs block, its corresponding kind and metadata in a single CL of infradata/config repo. I certainly don\u0027t want gce-provider to interpret only 33% or 67% of my change as it makes understanding the system harder.\n\n1) does LUCI-config guarantee that **eventually** (assuming nobody commits changes to infradata/config) revision of all configs used by gce-provider will be the same? AFAIU, the answer is yes since all config files are coming from the same configset (services/gce-provider).\n\n\n2) assuming 1), can MP wait instead till 1) is true instead?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 60,
        "endLine": 18,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "9b42c4d0d9ad2659dbfca0257bd7c12babc80d74",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a2053e8e_478c3a86",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 18,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-27T00:16:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem with #1 is that technically you can\u0027t assume nobody is committing any changes. What we were doing before was aborting if there was a revision mismatch and hoping that at some point there won\u0027t be a revision mismatch. In practice this is fine, but theoretically you may never be able to import a config under these circumstances.\n\nA better solution in my opinion would be to ask the config service for a config file at a specific revision. I asked for that feature but it doesn\u0027t look like it will be added any time soon: https://crbug.com/924787.\n\nAnyways, I\u0027ve changed back to the approach of failing on config mismatch and hoping that there won\u0027t be a mismatch at some point later on.",
      "parentUuid": "0ae7a0c2_c05a200b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 60,
        "endLine": 18,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "9b42c4d0d9ad2659dbfca0257bd7c12babc80d74",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bd424e85_94cd8192",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 18,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-27T03:43:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If your service retries more frequently than new commits gets processed by LUCI-config, it should be highly likely that you\u0027ll get consistent revision of all relevant files. So status quo - lgtm. Please update description.",
      "parentUuid": "a2053e8e_478c3a86",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 60,
        "endLine": 18,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "9b42c4d0d9ad2659dbfca0257bd7c12babc80d74",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
