    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b325f29_212c92bf",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/configs.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-25T01:21:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "GetVMs() is useful only if cfgs\u003d\u003dnil, but it\u0027s not clear why you\u0027d allow such a case.\n\nSimilarly throughout this CL, where it seems to me most changes from .XYZ to GetXYZ() weren\u0027t necessary",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "9b42c4d0d9ad2659dbfca0257bd7c12babc80d74",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8c986142_744d51b1",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/configs.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-27T00:16:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It should be allowed in general, cfgs can be a nil Configs. This time I\u0027ve been careful about where I changed to Get variants. For example, .Prefix on L28 doesn\u0027t need to be GetPrefix, because if you\u0027re iterating over cfgs.GetVMs(), then you have a non-nil Config so you can safely call .Prefix.\n\nBut at the top level, you can\u0027t be sure you have a non-nil Configs. Note that this is independent of how I actually use Configs elsewhere in the code. I believe it\u0027s the right thing to do for the function.",
      "parentUuid": "9b325f29_212c92bf",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "9b42c4d0d9ad2659dbfca0257bd7c12babc80d74",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
